DataElement.preferredName: Pulse Dye Laser Administered Dose Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The number used to represent the dose of intermittent occurrences characterized by a brief, sudden change in a quantity of a laser in which light is emitted by a fluorescent organic dye and which can be tuned to radiate at any of a wide range of frequencies.
